Steps to use this repository

1. Have React Native Expo installed
2. On a cell phone (with the developer/USB debugging feature enabled)
3. Cable

To install and download the repository:

1. Download the repository
2. Run the npm install command (to install all dependencies)
3. Check if all dependencies have been downloaded, with emphasis on react-native-ble-plx
4. Run npx expo prebuild
5. Connect the phone and enable the debugging sharing feature
6. Run npx expo run:android (to build and install the app on the phone)
7. To launch the Expo server again, run npx expo start --dev-client

To connect the BLE device to the app:

1. Enable Bluetooth
2. Follow the prompts in the app
3. Connect the device